---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---
<BaseLayout>
  <div class="container mx-auto px-4 py-8">
    <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold mb-6">Privacy Policy</h1>
    <p class="mb-4">Effective Date: September 2024</p>
    <p class="mb-4">At FoxFreela ("we," "us," "our"), your privacy is important to us. This Privacy Policy explains how we collect, use, and protect your personal information when you use our website https://www.foxfreela.com and services. It also explains your rights under the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR) and other relevant laws.</p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-6 mb-4">1. Data We Collect</h2>
    <p class="mb-4">We collect and process the following data through our website:</p>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-4 mb-2">a. Personal Data via Contact Forms</h3>
    <p class="mb-2">When you submit information through our contact forms, we may collect:</p>
    <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4">
      <li>Name</li>
      <li>Email address</li>
      <li>Budget (if provided)</li>
      <li>Phone number (if provided)</li>
      <li>How did you hear from us? (if provided)</li>
      <li>Plans</li>
      <li>Service</li>
      <li>Message content and any other details you voluntarily provide</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="mb-4"><strong>Purpose:</strong> This data is used to respond to your inquiries, provide support, or follow up on service requests.<br/><strong>Legal Basis:</strong> Consent and legitimate interest (responding to your inquiries).</p>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-4 mb-2">b. Analytics Data via Matomo</h3>
    <p class="mb-2">We use Matomo Analytics to collect anonymized data to understand how visitors interact with our website. The information collected includes:</p>
    <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4">
      <li>Anonymized IP addresses (Matomo anonymizes the last digits of the IP address to ensure it cannot be used to identify users)</li>
      <li>Device type, operating system, and browser information</li>
      <li>Referrer URL (the site you visited before arriving at ours)</li>
      <li>Pages visited and time spent on the site</li>
      <li>Interactions with our website (e.g., clicks, navigation)</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="mb-4"><strong>Purpose:</strong> This data is used to improve our website, enhance user experience, and monitor website performance.<br/><strong>Legal Basis:</strong> Legitimate interest (website performance and analytics).<br/><strong>Data Retention:</strong> Analytics data is retained for a period of [insert retention period], after which it is automatically deleted.</p>

    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-4 mb-2">c. Behavioral Data via Microsoft Clarity</h3>
    <p class="mb-2">We also use Microsoft Clarity to better understand how users interact with our website. The data collected includes:</p>
    <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4">
      <li>Click and scroll tracking</li>
      <li>Session replays</li>
      <li>Heatmaps to visualize how users engage with content</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="mb-4"><strong>Purpose:</strong> This information helps us optimize the website design and improve user experience.<br/><strong>Legal Basis:</strong> Consent (via cookie consent banner, where applicable).<br/><strong>Data Retention:</strong> Behavioral data collected by Microsoft Clarity is retained for [insert retention period] and anonymized as per Microsoft's data privacy policies.</p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-6 mb-4">2. How We Use the Data</h2>
    <p class="mb-2">We use the data collected for the following purposes:</p>
    <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4">
      <li>To respond to inquiries submitted through contact forms</li>
      <li>To monitor and improve our website's functionality and performance</li>
      <li>To enhance the user experience by understanding how visitors interact with the website</li>
      <li>To comply with legal obligations and protect our legitimate business interests</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-6 mb-4">3. Sharing Your Data</h2>
    <p class="mb-2">We do not sell or share your personal data with third parties, except in the following cases:</p>
    <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4">
      <li><strong>Service Providers:</strong> We may share anonymized data with third-party service providers to help improve our website or services, such as hosting providers or analytics tools (e.g., Matomo and Microsoft Clarity).</li>
      <li><strong>Legal Obligations:</strong> If required by law, we may disclose your information to public authorities or government agencies.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-6 mb-4">4. Data Retention</h2>
    <p class="mb-4">We retain your personal information for as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes for which it was collected, or as required by law. You can request deletion of your personal data at any time by contacting us.</p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-6 mb-4">5. Your Rights</h2>
    <p class="mb-2">Under GDPR, you have the following rights regarding your personal data:</p>
    <ul class="list-disc list-inside mb-4">
      <li><strong>Right to Access:</strong> You can request access to the data we have collected about you.</li>
      <li><strong>Right to Rectification:</strong> You can request corrections to any inaccurate or incomplete data.</li>
      <li><strong>Right to Erasure:</strong> You can request that we delete your personal data, subject to legal limitations.</li>
      <li><strong>Right to Restrict Processing:</strong> You can request that we restrict the processing of your data.</li>
      <li><strong>Right to Data Portability:</strong> You can request a copy of your data in a structured, commonly used, and machine-readable format.</li>
      <li><strong>Right to Object:</strong> You have the right to object to the processing of your personal data in certain circumstances, such as for marketing purposes.</li>
    </ul>
    <p class="mb-4">To exercise any of these rights, please contact us at [Your Email Address].</p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-6 mb-4">6. Cookies and Tracking Technologies</h2>
    <p class="mb-4">We use cookies and similar tracking technologies to enhance your browsing experience and analyze website traffic.</p>
    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-4 mb-2">a. Matomo Cookies</h3>
    <p class="mb-4">Matomo sets cookies to track user interactions with our website. These cookies help us collect anonymized data for analytics purposes. Matomo respects the 'Do Not Track' feature in browsers, so if you have it enabled, Matomo will not track your activities.</p>
    <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-4 mb-2">b. Microsoft Clarity Cookies</h3>
    <p class="mb-4">Microsoft Clarity uses cookies to collect user session data and track interactions like clicks and scrolls. You can control the use of these cookies through your browser settings or through our website's cookie consent banner.<br/><strong>Opt-Out:</strong> You can opt out of analytics and behavioral tracking by configuring your browser settings or by using the opt-out options provided in our cookie banner.</p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-6 mb-4">7. Data Security</h2>
    <p class="mb-4">We implement industry-standard security measures to protect your personal data from unauthorized access, disclosure, or loss. However, please be aware that no method of transmitting information over the internet is completely secure.</p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-6 mb-4">8. Changes to This Privacy Policy</h2>
    <p class="mb-4">We may update this Privacy Policy from time to time to reflect changes in our practices or legal requirements. We will notify you of any significant changes by posting the new Privacy Policy on our website and updating the effective date.</p>

    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mt-6 mb-4">9. Contact Us</h2>
    <p class="mb-2">If you have any questions or concerns regarding this Privacy Policy or your personal data, please contact us at:</p>
    <ul class="list-none mb-4">
      <li>Email: contact@foxfreela.com</li>
      <li>Phone: +49 174 6626856</li>
      <li>Address: Am Brungshof 1c, Siegburg - Germany</li>
    </ul>

    <div class="mt-8 pt-8 border-t">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold mb-4">Cookie consent</h2>
      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2">Privacy settings</h3>
      <p class="mb-4">We collect and process your data on this site to better understand how it is used. We always ask you for consent to do that. You can change your privacy settings here.</p>
      <button class="bg-blue-500 hover:bg-blue-700 text-white font-bold py-2 px-4 rounded">Manage settings</button>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-8 pt-8 border-t">
      <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mb-2">Data request</h3>
      <h4 class="text-lg font-semibold mb-2">Access to your data</h4>
      <p class="mb-4">Fill out the form to request access to your data. We'll only use your email to process this request.</p>
      <form>
        <div class="mb-4">
          <label class="block text-gray-700 text-sm font-bold mb-2" for="email">Email</label>
          <input class="shadow appearance-none border rounded w-full py-2 px-3 text-gray-700 leading-tight focus:outline-none focus:shadow-outline" id="email" type="email" placeholder="Email">
        </div>
        <div class="mb-4">
          <label class="block text-gray-700 text-sm font-bold mb-2" for="request-type">Request type</label>
          <select class="shadow appearance-none border rounded w-full py-2 px-3 text-gray-700 leading-tight focus:outline-none focus:shadow-outline" id="request-type">
            <option>Access to my data</option>
            <option>Delete my data</option>
            <option>Change my data</option>
          </select>
        </div>
        <div class="mb-4">
          <label class="block text-gray-700 text-sm font-bold mb-2" for="message">Message</label>
          <textarea class="shadow appearance-none border rounded w-full py-2 px-3 text-gray-700 leading-tight focus:outline-none focus:shadow-outline" id="message" placeholder="Message"></textarea>
        </div>
      </form>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout> 